headline: WM Q3 Deep Dive: Margin Pressures and Healthcare Integration Shape Outlook
summary: Waste management services provider Waste Management (NYSE:WM) missed Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q3 CY2025, but sales rose 14.9% year on year to $6.44 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.98 per share was 1.6% below analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Is Waste Management’s 7% Monthly Dip a Signal or a Short-Term Setback for Investors?
summary: Thinking about whether to stick with Waste Management or take your profits? You are definitely not alone. Investors have been watching the company closely as, after a stellar run over the last several years, the stock price has cooled off. Despite a nearly 93% gain across five years and a solid 37% bump over the past three, Waste Management has fallen 5% in the last week alone, capping off a roughly 7% dip this month. This kind of short-term volatility can feel unsettling, but it also raises...

headline: Waste Management (WM) Margin Decline Challenges Reliable Income Narrative Ahead of Slower Growth Forecasts
summary: Waste Management (WM) posted a 12% average annual increase in earnings over the last five years, but this year, earnings slipped, with net profit margins narrowing to 10.3% from 12.3% a year ago. Looking ahead, revenue is expected to grow by 5.7% annually and earnings by 13.6% per year, both trailing the broader US market. Still, the company is valued as a relative bargain based on its price-to-earnings ratio, pays an attractive dividend, and offers a steady profile for those prioritizing...
